      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2019: `loadMissingBodyOverwrites()` scans all `quickAccess` entries and can run repeatedly after every `loadConversation` / `loadSwarmUntil`. For large conversations this retriggers plugin transforms for every cached message missing `bodyOverwrite`, even when the current load request only fetched a small page. This can make history loading unexpectedly expensive. Limit the work to the messages returned by the load operation, or keep a per-plugin/per-message processed marker so messages known to have no overwrite are not recomputed on each load.",
