      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2257: The new plugin overwrite pass runs after `SwarmLoaded` is emitted, so the loaded payload still contains untransformed bodies and clients must wait for separate `SwarmMessageUpdated` signals. This contradicts the new `ChatHandler::transformSwarmMessages` contract saying it is called before `SwarmLoaded`, and can cause stale display/flicker or missed updates for clients that only process the load result. Move the overwrite loading/transform before emitting `SwarmLoaded`, or transform the `messages` vector before passing it to the signal.\n```suggestion\nif (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n    convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
